#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Script 1 — Extract SPC Training Dataset from PDF Books
=======================================================
Reads the Oakland and Zontec SPC books from /books/,
extracts relevant text chunks, and generates a JSONL
fine-tuning dataset saved to /output/spc-qa-pairs.jsonl.

The dataset has two parts:
  1. SEED pairs  — 60 hand-crafted, high-quality Q&A examples
                   that cover the most critical SPC concepts.
                   These are always included regardless of PDF quality.
  2. AUTO pairs  — Generated by wrapping extracted PDF text chunks
                   in explanation prompts. These grow automatically
                   as you add more PDFs to the books/ folder.

Run from Docker:
  docker compose -f docker-compose.train.yml run --rm extract
"""

